In this Presidential Memorandum, President Barack Obama establishes a task force called "Skills for America's Future" with the goal of developing innovative strategies to train more Americans with the skills needed for high-wage jobs in the 21st century. The task force will focus on partnerships between educational institutions, labor unions, small businesses, and other employers to create flexible and affordable training programs that meet regional and national economic needs. The task force will be led by the Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers, the Assistant to the President for Economic Policy, and the Assistant to the President for Domestic Policy, and will consist of various heads of executive departments and agencies. The task force's mission includes improving public-private collaboration, identifying opportunities for successful partnerships between trained workers and employers, developing stackable credentials for in-demand occupations, and utilizing technology for training and skills assessment. The memorandum also includes general provisions regarding implementation and assistance from executive departments and agencies.